  "texts": [
    "For example, the Coalition for Health AI, launched in 2022, brings together technologists, academics, policymakers, and health systems to help harmonize best practices for AI deployment and educate users about evaluating risks, benefits, and limitations.",
    "In July 2023, several leading AI companies committed to voluntary safeguards, such as conducting research to mitigate privacy concerns, testing products for security risks, and using watermarks for AI-generated content; in October, the Biden Administration issued an executive order requiring companies to notify the government and perform additional testing on models that could threaten public health and safety.",
    "These are important steps, but continued attention is needed to ensure that these innovative new technologies meet the time-tested standards of safe, high-quality medical care.",
    "Corresponding Author: Dhruv Khullar, MD, MPP; Department of Population Health Sciences, Weill Cornell Medicine, New York, NY, USA (e-mail: khd9010@med.cornell.edu)."
  ],
